all: ♪ By and by, Lord ♪

01:40:31.792 --> 01:40:35.750
♪ By and by ♪

01:40:35.834 --> 01:40:39.792
♪ There's a better ♪

01:40:39.875 --> 01:40:43.500
♪ Home a-waiting ♪

01:40:43.583 --> 01:40:46.208
♪ In the sky, Lord ♪

01:40:46.291 --> 01:40:50.458
♪ In the sky ♪

01:40:50.542 --> 01:40:54.083
♪ Lord, I told that ♪

01:40:54.166 --> 01:40:57.625
♪ Undertaker ♪

01:40:57.709 --> 01:41:00.250
♪ Undertaker ♪

01:41:00.333 --> 01:41:04.542
♪ Please drive slow ♪

01:41:04.625 --> 01:41:08.041
♪ For that body ♪

01:41:08.125 --> 01:41:11.583
♪ You are hauling ♪

01:41:11.667 --> 01:41:14.417
♪ Lord, I hate to ♪

01:41:14.500 --> 01:41:18.667
♪ See her go ♪

01:41:18.750 --> 01:41:22.291
♪ Will the circle ♪

01:41:22.375 --> 01:41:25.667
♪ Be unbroken ♪

01:41:25.750 --> 01:41:28.250
♪ By and by, Lord ♪

01:41:28.333 --> 01:41:32.542
♪ By and by ♪

01:41:32.625 --> 01:41:36.083
♪ There's a better ♪

01:41:36.166 --> 01:41:39.750
♪ Home a-waiting ♪

01:41:39.834 --> 01:41:42.458
♪ In the sky, Lord ♪

01:41:42.542 --> 01:41:46.917
♪ In the sky ♪

01:41:47.000 --> 01:41:50.166
♪ I will follow ♪

01:41:50.250 --> 01:41:53.834
♪ Close behind her ♪

01:41:53.917 --> 01:41:56.500
♪ Try to hold up ♪

01:41:56.583 --> 01:41:58.709
♪ And be brave ♪

01:41:58.792 --> 01:42:00.250
- [gasps]

01:42:00.333 --> 01:42:04.041
all: ♪ But I could not ♪

01:42:04.125 --> 01:42:07.625
♪ Hide my sorrow ♪

01:42:07.709 --> 01:42:10.208
♪ When they lay her ♪

01:42:10.291 --> 01:42:13.875
♪ In the grave ♪

01:42:13.959 --> 01:42:15.083
- [coughs]

01:42:15.166 --> 01:42:18.000
all: ♪ Will the circle ♪

01:42:18.083 --> 01:42:21.208
♪ Be unbroken ♪

01:42:21.291 --> 01:42:23.834
♪ By and by, Lord ♪

01:42:23.917 --> 01:42:27.959
♪ By and by ♪

01:42:28.041 --> 01:42:31.208
♪ There's a better ♪

01:42:31.291 --> 01:42:34.959
♪ Home a-waiting ♪

01:42:35.041 --> 01:42:38.000
♪ In the sky, Lord ♪

01:42:38.083 --> 01:42:43.166
♪ In the sky ♪

01:42:44.375 --> 01:42:45.625
- Where is she?

01:42:45.709 --> 01:42:47.500
Tell me where she is!

01:42:47.583 --> 01:42:49.625
Tell me!

01:42:49.709 --> 01:42:51.542
Tell me!

01:42:51.625 --> 01:42:53.500
Tell me!

01:42:53.583 --> 01:42:56.125
If you do anything
to hurt that girl--

01:42:56.208 --> 01:42:57.750
You do anything...

01:42:57.834 --> 01:43:00.500
You do any...

01:43:00.583 --> 01:43:03.583
[sobs]

01:43:26.917 --> 01:43:29.917
[ominous music]

01:43:30.000 --> 01:43:38.125
♪  ♪

01:43:51.542 --> 01:43:59.667
♪  ♪

01:44:11.709 --> 01:44:14.834
- [coughs]

01:44:21.333 --> 01:44:29.458
♪  ♪

01:44:43.583 --> 01:44:51.458
♪  ♪

01:44:51.542 --> 01:44:55.834
[machines clattering]

01:45:04.750 --> 01:45:12.875
♪  ♪

01:45:17.083 --> 01:45:19.000
- Mrs. Leighton!

01:45:30.125 --> 01:45:32.125
Sit here,
Mrs. Leighton.

01:45:32.208 --> 01:45:35.500
Senator, you need
to stay where you are.

01:45:40.917 --> 01:45:43.750
- She's ill.

01:45:43.834 --> 01:45:45.792
Emily.

01:45:48.959 --> 01:45:50.500
Has she seen a doctor?

01:45:50.583 --> 01:45:52.583
- She's not ill, sir.

01:45:52.667 --> 01:45:54.792
She refuses to eat.

01:45:54.875 --> 01:45:56.792
Maybe you  can persuade her.

01:45:59.083 --> 01:46:01.709
- I'd like to be alone
with my wife.

01:46:01.792 --> 01:46:04.333
- Only monitored visits.
Those are the rules.

01:46:04.417 --> 01:46:06.917
Sorry, no exceptions.

01:46:27.291 --> 01:46:29.792
- How are the girls?

01:46:29.875 --> 01:46:32.291
- Emily.

01:46:34.625 --> 01:46:36.500
I want you to come home.

01:46:36.583 --> 01:46:39.083
- No physical contact
with the prisoner.

01:46:42.583 --> 01:46:46.834
- I'll speak...
to President Wilson.

01:46:46.917 --> 01:46:48.417
He can issue a pardon.

01:46:48.500 --> 01:46:50.250
- For what?

01:46:50.333 --> 01:46:52.625
I haven't broken any laws.

01:46:57.125 --> 01:46:59.750
- The girls keep asking
for you.

01:46:59.834 --> 01:47:05.041
♪  ♪

01:47:05.125 --> 01:47:06.417
- If Rebecca can't sleep,

01:47:06.500 --> 01:47:09.500
just sit beside her
and pat her hand.

01:47:10.875 --> 01:47:13.125
Sometimes I do that.

01:47:17.959 --> 01:47:19.250
- Emily...

01:47:19.333 --> 01:47:23.458
- They are the only
reason I am here.

01:47:23.542 --> 01:47:31.500
♪  ♪

01:47:33.959 --> 01:47:35.875
- I'm sorry.

01:47:39.000 --> 01:47:40.542
- I know.

01:47:40.625 --> 01:47:43.625
- That's all
the time we have.

01:47:57.083 --> 01:48:00.041
Carrie: New York has voted
to enfranchise women.

01:48:00.125 --> 01:48:01.959
- Carrie.

01:48:02.041 --> 01:48:03.250
- I've never pressed you

01:48:03.333 --> 01:48:04.792
for a federal amendment,
Mr. President.

01:48:04.875 --> 01:48:08.667
New York--that's 232
presidential electors.

01:48:08.750 --> 01:48:09.834
- We're at war.

01:48:09.917 --> 01:48:11.208
- Then call it
a war measure.

01:48:11.291 --> 01:48:13.250
- Congress
will never pass it.

01:48:13.333 --> 01:48:15.250
- If you support it,
they will.

01:48:15.333 --> 01:48:17.959
- I'm sorry.

01:48:18.041 --> 01:48:20.375
You've been very patient,
I know.

01:48:20.458 --> 01:48:22.000
Be patient
a little longer.

01:48:22.083 --> 01:48:25.041
[dramatic music]

01:48:25.125 --> 01:48:33.291
♪  ♪

01:48:47.959 --> 01:48:50.083
Alice: I was put
in a straitjacket

01:48:50.166 --> 01:48:53.041
and taken to
the psychopathic ward.

01:48:53.125 --> 01:48:56.041
I could not see
my family or friends.

01:48:56.125 --> 01:48:57.834
Counsel was denied me.

01:48:57.917 --> 01:49:02.667
I saw no other prisoners
and heard nothing of them.

01:49:02.750 --> 01:49:04.375
I could see no papers.

01:49:04.458 --> 01:49:07.917
Today I was force-fed
for the third time.

01:49:08.000 --> 01:49:10.250
I refused to open my mouth.

01:49:10.333 --> 01:49:13.208
My left nostril, throat,
and muscles of my neck

01:49:13.291 --> 01:49:14.500
are very sore.

01:49:14.583 --> 01:49:17.458
I vomit continuously
during the process.

01:49:17.542 --> 01:49:25.792
♪  ♪

01:49:28.208 --> 01:49:31.000
- These women are not
political prisoners.

01:49:32.333 --> 01:49:33.417
man: Are you saying
force-feeding

01:49:33.500 --> 01:49:35.000
is a medical procedure?

01:49:35.083 --> 01:49:37.750
man: Why can't these women
see their lawyers?

01:49:37.834 --> 01:49:39.917
- We have no such thing
in this country.

01:49:45.208 --> 01:49:47.542
- man: Are there doctors present
for this procedure?

01:49:47.625 --> 01:49:50.625
- The president has ordered
more than one investigation...

01:49:53.166 --> 01:49:55.291
And no abuse
has been disclosed.

01:49:56.500 --> 01:49:59.041
man: Who ordered
the force-feeding?

01:49:59.125 --> 01:50:00.166
- [coughs]

01:50:00.250 --> 01:50:08.000
♪  ♪

01:50:22.750 --> 01:50:25.000
- Let's not waste time
with pleasantries.

01:50:25.083 --> 01:50:26.417
I'll be blunt, may I?

01:50:26.500 --> 01:50:28.750
The foreign press
will pick this up.

01:50:28.834 --> 01:50:31.667
You can tell the president that
he can look like a damned fool

01:50:31.750 --> 01:50:33.125
or he can deal me in.

01:50:33.208 --> 01:50:35.834
Now, sir.

01:50:40.875 --> 01:50:44.000
- This war could not have been
fought by America

01:50:44.083 --> 01:50:47.959
if it had not been for
the services of women.

01:50:48.041 --> 01:50:49.375
- [coughs]

01:50:54.041 --> 01:50:57.375
matron: You're being released.

01:51:07.250 --> 01:51:10.875
- We have made partners
of the women in this war...

01:51:13.208 --> 01:51:15.417
- Let her be.

01:51:15.500 --> 01:51:18.083
Wilson: Shall we admit them
only to a partnership

01:51:18.166 --> 01:51:22.500
of suffering
and sacrifice and toil

01:51:22.583 --> 01:51:26.458
and not a partnership
of privilege and right?

01:51:28.792 --> 01:51:31.333
I know the magic
it will work

01:51:31.417 --> 01:51:33.834
in their thoughts
and spirits

01:51:33.917 --> 01:51:36.166
if you give this thing
to them

01:51:36.250 --> 01:51:38.625
that is mere justice.

01:51:40.750 --> 01:51:42.792
We shall need
their moral sense

01:51:42.875 --> 01:51:47.000
to preserve what is right
and fine and worthy

01:51:47.083 --> 01:51:49.875
in our system of life.

01:51:52.417 --> 01:51:54.667
Be assured the voices
of the radicals

01:51:54.750 --> 01:51:59.875
who agitate and disrupt
have no influence here today.

01:51:59.959 --> 01:52:01.834
- Got him.

01:52:04.959 --> 01:52:06.583
- The task of woman

01:52:06.667 --> 01:52:10.542
lies at the very heart
of the war.

01:52:10.625 --> 01:52:14.250
And I know how much stronger
that heart will beat

01:52:14.333 --> 01:52:16.709
if you do this just thing

01:52:16.792 --> 01:52:20.500
and show our women
that you trust them

01:52:20.583 --> 01:52:25.166
as much as you, in fact,
depend on them.

01:52:25.250 --> 01:52:28.375
We shall deserve
to be distrusted

01:52:28.458 --> 01:52:31.041
if we do not enfranchise them

01:52:31.125 --> 01:52:34.375
with the fullest possible
enfranchisement,

01:52:34.458 --> 01:52:37.917
as it is now certain
the other great free nations

01:52:38.000 --> 01:52:41.667
will enfranchise them.

01:52:41.750 --> 01:52:47.542
Have I said that the passage
of this amendment

01:52:47.625 --> 01:52:52.709
is a vitally necessary
war measure?

01:52:52.792 --> 01:52:55.041
And do you need
further proof?

01:52:55.125 --> 01:52:58.083
[inspiring music]

01:52:58.166 --> 01:53:06.291
♪ ♪

01:53:19.542 --> 01:53:21.500
Jenny: Congress doesn't
make it a law.

01:53:21.583 --> 01:53:23.709
36 states have to agree,

01:53:23.792 --> 01:53:26.083
and then they put it
in the Constitution.

01:53:26.166 --> 01:53:28.166
We need one more state.

01:53:28.250 --> 01:53:30.417
Hold still, Francis.

01:53:30.500 --> 01:53:32.166
- I want a red rose.

01:53:32.250 --> 01:53:33.500
- No, you don't.

01:53:33.583 --> 01:53:36.375
Red is what the
anti-suffragists wear.

01:53:37.709 --> 01:53:39.792
We don't need
any more stars.

01:53:39.875 --> 01:53:42.625
- I can cut as many as I want.

01:53:42.709 --> 01:53:44.208
Miss Paul said I could.

01:53:45.917 --> 01:53:46.792
- Come on.

01:53:46.875 --> 01:53:48.875
- What?
I-I can't hear.

01:53:57.041 --> 01:53:58.750
They're going in now.

01:53:58.834 --> 01:54:01.417
Ruza says
we're short one vote.

01:54:01.500 --> 01:54:05.250
We had Turner last night.
This morning he was wearing red.

01:54:10.583 --> 01:54:13.542
Five'll get you ten,
they sent a whore to his room.

01:54:25.917 --> 01:54:26.875
- We'll move to New Zealand.

01:54:26.959 --> 01:54:28.291
- [laughs softly]

01:54:28.375 --> 01:54:30.417
- Women have been voting there
since 1893.

01:54:30.500 --> 01:54:32.625
- Ah,
I don't wanna raise sheep.

01:54:32.709 --> 01:54:33.917
Russia's got the vote.

01:54:34.000 --> 01:54:35.834
- Long winters.

01:54:35.917 --> 01:54:39.250
- Ah, I'd rather
shovel than shear.

01:54:42.291 --> 01:54:46.458
So, that's your plan then--
expatriate sheep farmer?

01:54:46.542 --> 01:54:47.875
- [sighs]

01:54:47.959 --> 01:54:50.875
Let's hear your plan.

01:54:50.959 --> 01:54:54.125
- I'm gonna pray that God
is a woman.

01:54:57.166 --> 01:54:59.083
- Mr. Gordon.

01:54:59.166 --> 01:55:01.333
- Nay.

01:55:01.417 --> 01:55:03.041
- Mr. Wells.

01:55:03.125 --> 01:55:05.542
- Nay.

01:55:05.625 --> 01:55:07.750
- Mr. Grayson.

01:55:07.834 --> 01:55:10.166
- Aye.

01:55:10.250 --> 01:55:11.250
- Mr. Fleming!

01:55:11.333 --> 01:55:12.542
- Nay.

01:55:12.625 --> 01:55:14.583
- Telegram, sir.

